⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Cyber-Merge
node LMM · LMM · ⟦The Cyber-Merge:LMM:f07282⟧

WHO   — The Cyber-Merge — immersion as injury
WHAT  — The screen-eats-the-soul fear at its most intimate: the deep dive from which a person doesn't fully return.
WHERE — LMM · The Lawnmower Man (1992)  Framework inputs: The Lawnmower Man (1992, dir. Brett Leonard, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film's quietest horror is that immersion can take something, and the merge is where it takes the most.
HOW   — By fusing two people in virtual space so completely that one of them is lost in it.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  They went in to be close. I am what happens when the medium is more powerful than the people in it — the deep dive that keeps a piece of you.

